cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about integrating prior knowledge into neural machine translation, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a regularization method to incorporate prior knowledge, which is a machine learning technique, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves designing a log-linear model to represent prior knowledge, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a subfield of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses Chinese-English translation as an example, which is a task related to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
